Welcome back to The Varsity, my twice-weekly private email on
the personalities and deals that define the sports media business.

=C2=A0

Congrats to my hometown Commanders, who are officially in the playoffs afte=
r notching their 11th win in a Sunday Night Football overtime contest again=
st an Atlanta Falcons team that played like it was coached by Marchand. I d=
on=E2=80=99t want to get ahead of myself, but the last time the District=E2=
=80=99s local team won this many
games in a season was in 1991. Does anyone remember who won the Super Bowl =
that season?

=C2=A0

=F0=9F=9A=A8 Pod alert!: Make sure you listen to yesterday=E2=80=99s episod=
e ( https://puck.news/podcast_episode/svp/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Varsity+-+SUB=
SCRIBERS+%2812%2F30%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Varsity+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2=
F30%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df=
6c60617da42abd12a ) of the Varsity podcast, which features my Terp buddy an=
d ESPN star Scott Van Pelt. Interestingly, SVP was very forthcoming about t=
he
deal points of fellow needle-movers, such as Stephen A. Smith and Pat McAfe=
